<dl id="n08153e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08153e">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08153e"> 153(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ 7 days fast / 9 times round isle / locked 24 hours in cave / (Tophonius) entrance to / purgatory / range of stones &mdash; saints / vicarious penances / drawbridge / pickled lax / Coleraine </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Lough Derg is a lake in Co. Donegal, famous as the traditional scene of St. Patrick&apos;s purgatory. Coleraine is a seaport and market town of Co. Londonderry, Ireland. </mm> </dd></dl>
